decision_conditions:
Condition : 2 - Affordable housing. The development shall not be occupied until a Section 106 agreement or other a legally binding agreement between the Council and an external housing delivery body, including a registered provider (in the event that the Council retains ownership of the site), has been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority.
The agreement shall include:
The numbers, type and location of the affordable housing provision; 
A minimum of 50% of the habitable rooms in the development; 
A tenure split of the units comprising, a minimum of 30 per cent low-cost rented homes, as either London Affordable Rent or Social Rent, allocated according to need and for Londoners on low incomes, 30 per cent of the remaining units as intermediate products which meet the definition of genuinely affordable housing, including London Living Rent and London Shared ownership, 40 per cent of the remaining units to be determined by the borough as low-cost rented homes or intermediate products, to a minimum of 0 percent of intermediate products in the event that all units are delivered as low cost rented homes. 
The timing of the construction and availability of the affordable housing as a part of the overall development; 
Arrangements to ensure that such provision is affordable for both first and subsequent  occupiers of the affordable housing; and
The occupancy criteria to be used for determining the identity of occupiers of the affordable housing, and the means by which such occupancy criteria shall be enforced.
Reason for condition. To ensure that the development fulfils strategic and local planning housing objectives to provide affordable housing and to comply with London Plan (2021) policies H4, H5 and H6.

Condition : 5 - Off site tree panting. The development shall not commence until a Section 106 agreement, or other legally binding agreement between the Council and the site owner or between the Council and a housing delivery body contracted to deliver the development, including a registered provider, in the event that the Council retains ownership of the site, for a scheme of off-site tree planting in Mitcham.
The offsite tree planting scheme shall:
Identify the locations and quantify the value of the trees to be removed using CAVAT methodology;
Identify the locations, species, size and costs of replacements trees;
Agree the timing of planting of replacement trees and measures for their on-going maintenance and replacement where necessary, over a period of not less than 10 years from planting.

Reason for condition. To ensure that suitable mitigation measures are in place to provide for the replacement and long term management of replacement trees in the interests of maintaining and enhancing the visual amenities of the public realm and streetscape in Mitcham, and to comply with London Plan (2021) policy D4, G5, G6 and G7 and Merton Sites and Policies Plan (2014) policies DM 02, and DM D2.
